<assessment id="_u5_calcium-deficiency-inline">
    <title>Calcium
        <?oxy_comment_start author="michellemyers" timestamp="20111217T003724-0500" comment="I did not read this file because it wasn&apos;t linked to, and the qestion is repeated in another file."?>Deficiency<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
    <page>
        <question id="_u5_calcium-deficiency-inline1">
            <body>What would be the result of a calcium deficiency?</body>
            <multiple_choice shuffle="false" id="ans">
                <choice value="weak_bones">weak bones</choice>
                <choice value="poorly_formed">poorly formed hydroxyapetite</choice>
                <choice value="increase_risk">increased risk of fracture</choice>
                <choice value="all_above">all of the above </choice>
            </multiple_choice>
            <part>
                <response match="weak_bones" score="0">
                    <feedback>While weak bones is a result of calcium deficiency, there are other consequences of low calcium levels.</feedback>
                </response>
                <response match="poorly_formed" score="0">
                    <feedback>While poorly formed hydroxyapetite is a result of calcium deficiency, there are other consequences of low calcium levels.</feedback>
                </response>
                <response match="increase_risk" score="0">
                    <feedback>While increased risk of fracture is a result of calcium deficiency, there are other consequences of low calcium levels.</feedback>
                </response>
                <response match="all_above" score="1">
                    <feedback>That's right! Calcium is also important for overall body function including most cell function, most importantly in nerve and muscle function.</feedback>
                </response>
                <hint>There are many length scales that would be impacted with a loss of calcium.</hint>
            </part>
        </question>

